Generates some synthetic 1-dimensional data with three clusters. Returns a data frame with (1) time, (2) Y (3) mu (4) cluster assignments.

gendat_1d.Rd

Generates some synthetic 1-dimensional data with three clusters. Returns a data frame with (1) time, (2) Y (3) mu (4) cluster assignments.

Usage

gendat_1d(TT, ntlist, offset = 0, return_model = FALSE, sd3 = NULL)

Arguments

TT

Number of time points.

offset

Defaults to 0. How much to push up cluster 1.

return_model

If true, return true cluster means and probabilities instead of data.

nt

Number of particles at each time.

Value

long matrix with data or model.
